cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on the application of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for semantic segmentation of brain MRI images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes different ways to introduce spatial constraints into the network, which involves the use of machine learning techniques such as deep learning and optimization algorithms. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could also classify it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
